WEBVTT

00:00:00.040 --> 00:00:14.740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

00:00:43.210 --> 00:00:48.424
CHAPTER 39: USE A BIT OF SENSE AND FIGURE IT OUT YOURSELF

00:00:48.883 --> 00:00:51.677
Mr. Ga! Wait a minute.

00:00:51.761 --> 00:00:53.429
Sir! I have something to say!

00:00:53.512 --> 00:00:55.222
Just a moment. Wait.

00:00:55.306 --> 00:00:56.891
Just a second.

00:01:01.145 --> 00:01:02.146
Just a moment.

00:01:05.900 --> 00:01:06.984
What is it?

00:01:16.118 --> 00:01:17.161
I…

00:01:23.083 --> 00:01:24.126
I…

00:01:28.214 --> 00:01:30.925
I'm struggling with the after-school math.

00:01:37.348 --> 00:01:38.182
What?

00:01:40.059 --> 00:01:40.893
You know,

00:01:41.852 --> 00:01:43.437
I…

00:01:45.606 --> 00:01:47.983
I keep skipping the homework,

00:01:48.067 --> 00:01:51.237
and I feel like I'm holding the other girls back.

00:01:52.488 --> 00:01:54.448
It's weighing on my heart.

00:01:54.532 --> 00:01:56.492
I feel so guilty, sir.

00:02:00.287 --> 00:02:02.581
So you get no desire at all to learn more?

00:02:03.749 --> 00:02:05.793
What happened to the promise you made ten years ago?

00:02:06.418 --> 00:02:08.045
You talked so big back then.

00:02:09.839 --> 00:02:10.714
Sorry?

00:02:11.465 --> 00:02:12.508
I'm talking about you.

00:02:13.217 --> 00:02:14.260
Eui-ju.

00:02:17.847 --> 00:02:19.557
I what?

00:02:20.558 --> 00:02:23.644
I really believed you would be good at math.

00:02:27.940 --> 00:02:28.941
You're saying

00:02:29.775 --> 00:02:31.986
I made a promise to you?

00:02:32.069 --> 00:02:33.195
What promise?

00:02:34.655 --> 00:02:35.698
Forget it.

00:02:37.366 --> 00:02:38.450
What?

00:02:38.534 --> 00:02:39.952
Mr. Ga, wait.

00:02:40.035 --> 00:02:40.953
EPISODE 13

00:02:41.036 --> 00:02:43.706
Tell me what promise I made.

00:02:43.789 --> 00:02:44.915
Mr. Ga!

00:02:46.917 --> 00:02:48.377
Did you tidy the classroom?

00:02:50.212 --> 00:02:51.046
Oh, right.

00:02:54.758 --> 00:02:55.885
Goodbye.

00:03:15.195 --> 00:03:16.113
Promise?

00:03:17.156 --> 00:03:20.034
I can't do it.

00:03:20.117 --> 00:03:22.119
I just can't.

00:03:22.202 --> 00:03:23.871
Then write him a letter.

00:03:24.455 --> 00:03:25.331
A letter?

00:03:25.414 --> 00:03:26.665
Sure, you're a writer.

00:03:26.749 --> 00:03:27.958
Use your words to shoot your shot.

00:03:30.294 --> 00:03:31.211
Shoot my shot?

00:03:36.050 --> 00:03:39.261
WE WERE FRIENDS, EPISODE 9

00:03:44.016 --> 00:03:45.017
I'm here.

00:03:47.811 --> 00:03:51.482
Why didn't I think of this before?

00:03:52.775 --> 00:03:56.236
All I had to do was tell him how I felt through my work.

00:03:56.862 --> 00:03:58.238
Dig in. I know you're hungry.

00:03:58.322 --> 00:03:59.531
Thanks.

00:04:04.370 --> 00:04:05.579
Are you really choosing me,

00:04:06.080 --> 00:04:08.958
or are you just running away from Tae-ha?

00:04:09.750 --> 00:04:12.044
-Is there a difference? -There's a huge difference!

00:04:15.547 --> 00:04:17.007
I don't want to be your refuge.

00:04:18.384 --> 00:04:20.219
It's just hard thinking about Tae-ha.

00:04:21.637 --> 00:04:23.931
It's easier, being around you.

00:04:24.556 --> 00:04:25.849
Easier?

00:04:26.517 --> 00:04:27.559
So that's what I am to you.

00:04:29.228 --> 00:04:30.354
That's kind of harsh.

00:04:32.231 --> 00:04:34.441
Sorry for being so selfish.

00:04:34.525 --> 00:04:36.026
It's fine, since I'm selfish myself.

00:04:37.027 --> 00:04:39.279
If I'm by your side when you're confused,

00:04:39.363 --> 00:04:40.948
you might end up choosing me.

00:04:41.031 --> 00:04:44.743
IN THAT MOMENT, YOON DECIDED TO SHOOT HIS SHOT

00:04:45.953 --> 00:04:47.454
Si-on, I like you.

00:04:47.538 --> 00:04:54.044
SI-ON, I LIKE YOU

00:04:54.837 --> 00:04:56.088
To tell the truth,

00:04:57.339 --> 00:04:59.425
I've liked you for a long time.

00:04:59.508 --> 00:05:00.592
Since high school.

00:05:04.138 --> 00:05:06.015
If I didn't tell you today,

00:05:06.098 --> 00:05:07.808
I think I'd regret it for the rest of my life.

00:05:17.317 --> 00:05:18.861
How can you not know how I feel?

00:05:18.944 --> 00:05:20.029
Do I have to spell it out?

00:05:20.112 --> 00:05:22.531
Can't you use a bit of sense and figure it out yourself?

00:05:26.243 --> 00:05:27.286
I like you.

00:05:27.369 --> 00:05:29.329
Every time you look at me,

00:05:30.122 --> 00:05:32.541
I feel like my heart's going to explode.

00:05:33.292 --> 00:05:34.835
When you so much as pass me by,

00:05:35.461 --> 00:05:36.712
my heart flutters.

00:05:37.921 --> 00:05:39.173
Even now.

00:05:39.256 --> 00:05:41.675
Even when you picked on me and acted all mean.

00:05:41.759 --> 00:05:43.927
Even when you humiliated me for being terrible at math.

00:05:45.220 --> 00:05:47.139
I never hated you.

00:05:47.681 --> 00:05:49.725
I like you. I like you, okay?

00:05:49.808 --> 00:05:51.810
I really like you, Si-on!

00:05:56.023 --> 00:05:57.066
I like you.

00:06:09.745 --> 00:06:10.871
So,

00:06:10.954 --> 00:06:12.664
you didn't write the letter?

00:06:12.748 --> 00:06:13.874
Well…

00:06:13.957 --> 00:06:15.959
I'll do it some other time.

00:06:16.043 --> 00:06:17.836
Jeez. Some other time when?

00:06:18.921 --> 00:06:21.131
Even if I confess my feelings,

00:06:21.757 --> 00:06:23.092
will anything change?

00:06:23.759 --> 00:06:27.262
Let's say I work up the courage to tell him I like him.

00:06:27.346 --> 00:06:30.432
What then? It's not like he's going to reciprocate.

00:06:31.809 --> 00:06:33.685
-Good morning. -Good morning.

00:06:33.769 --> 00:06:35.062
Good morning.

00:06:40.192 --> 00:06:42.486
Go talk to him.

00:06:42.569 --> 00:06:43.862
Go.

00:06:45.114 --> 00:06:46.532
Mr. Ga.

00:06:46.615 --> 00:06:48.158
Well…

00:06:48.242 --> 00:06:50.244
I uploaded a new episode yesterday.

00:06:50.327 --> 00:06:52.746
Did you get a chance to see it?

00:06:52.830 --> 00:06:54.331
What did you think?

00:06:56.416 --> 00:06:58.710
It was weird how Yoon changed so much.

00:06:59.503 --> 00:07:01.839
Why would he say that? That came out of nowhere.

00:07:07.928 --> 00:07:09.054
What's wrong?

00:07:10.013 --> 00:07:11.849
Why? What did he say?

00:07:11.932 --> 00:07:12.850
It was nothing.

00:07:15.144 --> 00:07:16.228
-Let's just go. -Huh?

00:07:18.313 --> 00:07:20.691
-Good morning. -Good morning.

00:07:21.900 --> 00:07:23.527
Did you all bring your assignments?

00:07:23.610 --> 00:07:24.444
-Yes. -Yes.

00:07:24.528 --> 00:07:26.238
Hand them in now. Don't do them in class.

00:07:26.321 --> 00:07:27.281
Pass them forward.

00:07:27.364 --> 00:07:28.240
-Okay. -Okay.

00:07:29.533 --> 00:07:30.659
-Hang on. -Just a sec.

00:07:42.671 --> 00:07:43.672
Did anyone not do it?

00:07:47.009 --> 00:07:47.843
Me, sir.

00:07:50.012 --> 00:07:51.430
Stand up, Eui-ju.

00:07:55.934 --> 00:07:57.186
Why didn't you do it?

00:07:57.936 --> 00:07:59.229
I forgot, sir.

00:08:00.230 --> 00:08:01.190
Forgot?

00:08:01.815 --> 00:08:02.983
What happened to your priorities?

00:08:04.151 --> 00:08:07.029
Shouldn't your top priorities be studying and working on homework?

00:08:07.112 --> 00:08:08.280
Am I wrong?

00:08:09.990 --> 00:08:11.408
Are you going to keep this up?

00:08:13.076 --> 00:08:14.119
No, sir.

00:08:14.203 --> 00:08:17.080
I want you to do the original assignment plus some advanced problems by tomorrow.

00:08:18.999 --> 00:08:20.042
Yes, sir.

00:08:20.125 --> 00:08:21.126
Sit down.

00:08:27.007 --> 00:08:28.091
All right, turn to page 99.

00:08:28.175 --> 00:08:30.260
Did you do something wrong?

00:08:30.344 --> 00:08:32.054
Why is he so harsh on you?

00:08:32.930 --> 00:08:34.264
I don't know.

00:08:34.348 --> 00:08:35.474
I'm screwed.

00:08:40.270 --> 00:08:41.563
Why is he so uptight?

00:08:41.647 --> 00:08:43.023
CHAPTER 40: YOU THINK YOU COULD HIDE IT?

00:08:43.106 --> 00:08:44.691
That pop quiz we took in math.

00:08:44.775 --> 00:08:46.443
Mr. Ga said no half marks.

00:08:47.486 --> 00:08:48.820
He has no compassion.

00:08:49.446 --> 00:08:50.697
It's like he's AI.

00:08:52.074 --> 00:08:54.076
Isn't he just following the rules?

00:08:54.993 --> 00:08:56.495
That might actually be more fair.

00:08:57.162 --> 00:08:59.039
What are you talking about?

00:08:59.122 --> 00:09:01.458
So what if he's got a pretty face?

00:09:01.541 --> 00:09:03.001
Exactly.

00:09:03.085 --> 00:09:04.294
That's what's even more annoying.

00:09:04.378 --> 00:09:06.672
He's so handsome like a prince charming,

00:09:07.297 --> 00:09:08.674
but his personality sucks.

00:09:08.757 --> 00:09:10.509
It really ruins the fantasy.

00:09:10.592 --> 00:09:13.053
His personality isn't that bad.

00:09:13.136 --> 00:09:14.137
He's just a bit spiky.

00:09:20.018 --> 00:09:21.687
What's up with you today?

00:09:21.770 --> 00:09:23.689
You used to talk crap about him all the time.

00:09:24.564 --> 00:09:26.108
Why are you taking his side?

00:09:28.610 --> 00:09:30.779
Me? When did I do that?

00:09:34.992 --> 00:09:35.826
By any chance,

00:09:36.952 --> 00:09:38.078
do you have a crush on him?

00:09:41.707 --> 00:09:42.749
Hey.

00:09:43.250 --> 00:09:44.876
Watch what you say.

00:09:45.460 --> 00:09:46.336
She's not crazy.

00:09:47.546 --> 00:09:48.505
Right.

00:09:49.089 --> 00:09:50.340
I took it too far.

00:09:50.841 --> 00:09:52.384
You crossed the line.

00:09:52.467 --> 00:09:53.802
Sorry. My bad.

00:09:53.885 --> 00:09:55.429
Let's go. See you later, Eui-ju.

00:09:59.599 --> 00:10:01.143
You idiot.

00:10:01.226 --> 00:10:04.604
They say you can't hide love and a cough, kiddo.

00:10:04.688 --> 00:10:06.982
Have I been found out? Do you think they caught on?

00:10:08.525 --> 00:10:09.735
I'd better be careful.

00:10:12.529 --> 00:10:14.031
Isn't the school in that web novel

00:10:14.114 --> 00:10:15.198
just like ours?

00:10:15.282 --> 00:10:17.743
-You think? -The characters are like our teachers.

00:10:17.826 --> 00:10:20.787
The ice hockey player Tae-ha is Mr. Jung, and the rich returning student is Mr. Noh.

00:10:21.413 --> 00:10:22.748
Hey, check this out.

00:10:23.373 --> 00:10:27.085
"He always wears a beige cardigan and an old brown leather-band watch."

00:10:27.169 --> 00:10:29.004
That's Mr. Yoon.

00:10:29.087 --> 00:10:30.797
You're right. I saw him earlier.

00:10:30.881 --> 00:10:32.841
He was wearing that cardigan again.

00:10:32.924 --> 00:10:34.009
I'm telling you I'm right.

00:10:34.092 --> 00:10:36.011
The other one is definitely Mr. Ga.

00:10:36.094 --> 00:10:38.138
The other day in class,

00:10:38.221 --> 00:10:40.599
I saw how he always crooks his pinky when he adjusts his glasses.

00:10:40.682 --> 00:10:42.225
-Really? -Five times out of five.

00:10:42.309 --> 00:10:43.310
That's just like Si-on.

00:10:43.894 --> 00:10:45.562
I'm shipping Si-on with Yoon.

00:10:45.645 --> 00:10:47.439
I'm all for Tae-ha and Yoon.

00:10:47.522 --> 00:10:48.357
WE WERE FRIENDS

00:10:48.440 --> 00:10:49.274
Ju Si-on?

00:10:49.358 --> 00:10:50.817
-Kang Tae-ha? -Look.

00:10:51.401 --> 00:10:52.611
Choi Yoon?

00:10:53.111 --> 00:10:54.738
…AND TURNS HIS WATCH TO LOOK AT IT

00:11:04.664 --> 00:11:06.666
"Si-on said,

00:11:06.750 --> 00:11:08.794
-'When a star is born…'" -When a star is born,

00:11:08.877 --> 00:11:10.712
countless clouds of dust surround it so densely

00:11:10.796 --> 00:11:11.963
you can't even see an inch ahead.

00:11:12.047 --> 00:11:13.423
That's why people say…

00:11:13.507 --> 00:11:16.927
"That's why people say stars are born out of chaos."

00:11:17.010 --> 00:11:20.347
This problem might seem complicated, but you'll find that it's actually simple.

00:11:20.972 --> 00:11:22.516
In fact, no math problem

00:11:23.392 --> 00:11:24.976
can ever be as complicated as life.

00:11:26.478 --> 00:11:29.189
Those are all things Mr. Ga said.

00:11:30.148 --> 00:11:31.733
Does this mean the writer

00:11:32.651 --> 00:11:34.194
is in our class?

00:11:35.195 --> 00:11:36.363
And in after-school math?

00:11:37.864 --> 00:11:39.658
Put some heart into it, okay? Hey, Ms. Eui-ju.

00:11:39.741 --> 00:11:40.826
Put some heart into it.

00:11:40.909 --> 00:11:43.120
Your drawings must suck for her to be like this, girl.

00:11:43.203 --> 00:11:45.038
-Let me tell you about drawing… -Unbelievable.

00:11:45.872 --> 00:11:47.416
What do you know about drawing?

00:11:47.499 --> 00:11:49.501
-Okay, Picasso. -Give me a break.

00:11:49.584 --> 00:11:50.919
Okay.

00:11:51.002 --> 00:11:53.004
Eui-ju is the only one who fits the bill.

00:11:57.467 --> 00:11:59.719
-This is great. -Jenny, what are you reading?

00:12:00.387 --> 00:12:02.347
Fifty Shades of Mr. CEO.

00:12:03.432 --> 00:12:06.143
The male lead has finally confessed his feelings.

00:12:06.226 --> 00:12:07.227
No way! How did he do it?

00:12:08.728 --> 00:12:09.771
Like this.

00:12:09.855 --> 00:12:10.897
And then.

00:12:12.524 --> 00:12:14.568
"You know I can't live without you."

00:12:15.652 --> 00:12:16.778
"How could you resign?"

00:12:19.114 --> 00:12:22.993
According to the comments, she goes to his place in the next episode.

00:12:23.076 --> 00:12:25.162
I guess he's going to pretend to be sick.

00:12:25.245 --> 00:12:26.955
It's such a cliché.

00:12:27.956 --> 00:12:31.585
But even though it's clichéd, people still go crazy for it.

00:12:31.668 --> 00:12:34.171
This is so cringe, but why is it so good?

00:12:34.254 --> 00:12:38.758
Romance novels are such a classic for a reason!

00:12:38.842 --> 00:12:39.885
You're so right.

00:12:39.968 --> 00:12:43.680
Works of mega-hit writers are all quite similar, right?

00:12:43.763 --> 00:12:45.265
Why? Is it not going well?

00:12:45.348 --> 00:12:46.641
You said you were done.

00:12:46.725 --> 00:12:48.727
You'll keep it a secret even if you hit the big time?

00:12:48.810 --> 00:12:49.853
The big time?

00:12:51.396 --> 00:12:54.858
-You'll be the first one I tell. -That's right.

00:12:57.861 --> 00:12:58.695
I'm at school.

00:12:59.279 --> 00:13:00.489
It's all right. I can talk.

00:13:02.073 --> 00:13:04.493
That movie we saw? Of course, I remember.

00:13:05.619 --> 00:13:06.745
It's getting a sequel?

00:13:06.828 --> 00:13:08.288
Really?

00:13:10.665 --> 00:13:12.501
I guess it's that woman from the other day.

00:13:14.961 --> 00:13:16.087
I haven't seen it.

00:13:16.171 --> 00:13:17.506
What's so funny?

00:13:30.644 --> 00:13:33.563
Shouldn't your top priorities be studying and working on homework?

00:13:33.647 --> 00:13:34.481
Am I wrong?

00:13:38.235 --> 00:13:40.111
Why would he say that? That came out of nowhere.

00:13:52.123 --> 00:13:55.210
He's never smiled at me like that.

00:13:59.172 --> 00:14:01.132
Is this what you call L-O-V-E?

00:14:02.842 --> 00:14:04.970
How have you managed to endure this so many times?

00:14:05.887 --> 00:14:07.931
It's killing me.

00:14:08.557 --> 00:14:10.642
You learn from the pain and grow.

00:14:14.854 --> 00:14:16.481
I just wish it were all a novel.

00:14:18.066 --> 00:14:19.776
Then everything would be just as I wanted.

00:14:20.860 --> 00:14:23.238
From confessing my feelings to the aftermath and the ending,

00:14:24.656 --> 00:14:26.491
everything would go just as I'd like then.

00:14:27.617 --> 00:14:29.911
So? Are you just going to give up?

00:14:31.955 --> 00:14:34.874
I haven't even started. What is there to give up?

00:14:36.042 --> 00:14:37.586
What did I tell you?

00:14:37.669 --> 00:14:40.046
With L-O-V-E, you just have to go straight for it.

00:14:41.256 --> 00:14:42.090
No.

00:14:44.884 --> 00:14:45.969
I won't.

00:14:48.346 --> 00:14:50.140
I'm done, Go-ya.

00:14:51.600 --> 00:14:53.018
If I keep going,

00:14:53.810 --> 00:14:55.562
I feel like I'll get hit by a bike

00:14:55.645 --> 00:14:58.815
and then by a car doing 140 kmph.

00:14:59.482 --> 00:15:01.109
I'll just end up a bloody mess.

00:15:04.154 --> 00:15:06.114
It's hard enough already.

00:15:08.325 --> 00:15:09.784
I'm just going to stop here.

00:15:13.663 --> 00:15:15.874
Mr. Ga sees her in a romantic light,

00:15:15.957 --> 00:15:17.083
but not me.

00:15:20.253 --> 00:15:22.505
That's not going to change no matter what I do.

00:15:23.882 --> 00:15:25.550
Besides, more than anything,

00:15:26.676 --> 00:15:27.927
he looks happy.

00:15:30.305 --> 00:15:31.640
Isn't that what matters?

00:15:35.727 --> 00:15:36.728
You poor thing.

00:15:50.450 --> 00:15:52.118
This tastes amazing.

00:15:53.787 --> 00:15:55.830
Hey, where were you off to today?

00:15:57.207 --> 00:15:59.668
Did you go hang out with your friend Deul-i?

00:16:00.251 --> 00:16:01.169
Don't be ridiculous.

00:16:01.252 --> 00:16:02.671
She's gone back to Seoul.

00:16:02.754 --> 00:16:04.089
No way.

00:16:05.131 --> 00:16:06.299
I can tell you met her.

00:16:07.300 --> 00:16:08.343
Are you two an item now,

00:16:08.843 --> 00:16:10.261
or is this a rekindled thing

00:16:10.929 --> 00:16:12.764
after breaking up back in the day?

00:16:12.847 --> 00:16:13.682
Just eat your dinner.

00:16:14.516 --> 00:16:15.517
He's changing the subject.

00:16:16.685 --> 00:16:18.228
What's wrong?

00:16:18.311 --> 00:16:19.229
Are you shy about it?

00:16:19.813 --> 00:16:21.189
Is that what's up, little Woo-su?

00:16:21.940 --> 00:16:23.066
So cute!

00:16:23.817 --> 00:16:26.236
He said he didn't, so give it a rest.

00:16:26.319 --> 00:16:27.320
Eat your dinner.

00:16:27.404 --> 00:16:28.947
Hey.

00:16:29.030 --> 00:16:30.949
Think about the countless women

00:16:31.032 --> 00:16:33.576
hooked by his looks but turned off by his personality.

00:16:33.660 --> 00:16:34.536
Oh, those poor girls.

00:16:34.619 --> 00:16:35.954
-Tons of them. -That's true.

00:16:36.996 --> 00:16:39.999
I've always been worried that his long-term singleness would make him

00:16:40.083 --> 00:16:43.169
a toxic person who'd curse the world…

00:16:43.795 --> 00:16:44.671
Hey!

00:16:44.754 --> 00:16:45.880
-Dust. -It doesn't hurt.

00:16:45.964 --> 00:16:46.881
I know all your moves.

00:16:46.965 --> 00:16:48.633
-Zero pain. -You're still getting hit.

00:16:48.717 --> 00:16:50.552
-It doesn't hurt at all. -Hey, we're eating here.

00:16:50.635 --> 00:16:52.137
-Are you kids, or what? -No pain at all.

00:16:52.220 --> 00:16:53.304
-Jeez. -You can't even dodge.

00:16:53.388 --> 00:16:54.973
-Guys. -I'm landing twice as many hits!

00:16:57.976 --> 00:17:00.520
-Yoon's confession, what a twist! -I never imagined Yoon would do that.

00:17:00.603 --> 00:17:02.147
Logically, it doesn't make sense,

00:17:02.230 --> 00:17:03.565
but emotionally, it's perfect.

00:17:04.315 --> 00:17:05.150
See?

00:17:05.233 --> 00:17:07.610
Everyone loves Yoon's confession.

00:17:07.694 --> 00:17:08.903
Why did he say it's weird?

00:17:16.536 --> 00:17:18.538
Does the writer go to Murim Girls' High?

00:17:25.295 --> 00:17:26.212
What the heck?

00:17:26.838 --> 00:17:28.006
What the heck is this?

00:17:28.506 --> 00:17:29.758
Is this someone from school?

00:17:30.842 --> 00:17:32.427
This must be just a lucky guess, right?

00:17:34.888 --> 00:17:36.973
Hands up if you're still up!

00:18:02.999 --> 00:18:05.794
DOES THE WRITER GO TO MURIM GIRLS' HIGH?

00:18:07.170 --> 00:18:08.505
Do you read web novels?

00:18:08.588 --> 00:18:10.799
Not recently.

00:18:10.882 --> 00:18:11.883
Why? Do you?

00:18:12.509 --> 00:18:14.052
No, not me.

00:18:14.135 --> 00:18:16.054
There's a web novel with main characters

00:18:16.596 --> 00:18:19.307
who are exactly like the Korean literature, Math, PE,

00:18:19.390 --> 00:18:22.060
and Japanese teachers from our school.

00:18:22.143 --> 00:18:23.102
Huh? Really?

00:18:23.186 --> 00:18:24.437
Yeah.

00:18:24.521 --> 00:18:26.606
One of the main characters is a math genius.

00:18:26.689 --> 00:18:29.484
Apparently, his personality is just like Mr. Ga's.

00:18:30.151 --> 00:18:31.194
Isn't that weird?

00:18:31.277 --> 00:18:32.862
-No way. -I know.

00:18:32.946 --> 00:18:35.448
I'm really curious who wrote it.

00:18:35.907 --> 00:18:38.701
If it were me, I wouldn't be able to keep it a secret.

00:18:39.869 --> 00:18:41.329
Eui-ju, what do you think?

00:18:43.581 --> 00:18:44.541
About what?

00:18:45.250 --> 00:18:46.918
If it were you, do you think you could hide it?

00:18:49.170 --> 00:18:50.129
Hide what?

00:18:52.966 --> 00:18:55.718
I was just asking. Why are you getting so serious?

00:19:12.151 --> 00:19:13.111
So good.

00:19:13.903 --> 00:19:15.196
-Sexy food. -Love the soup.

00:19:15.780 --> 00:19:16.739
Sexy food.

00:19:16.823 --> 00:19:19.075
She said it like she had it all figured out.

00:19:20.326 --> 00:19:22.078
-This tastes great. -Right?

00:19:22.871 --> 00:19:25.123
Did you hand in your math assignment?

00:19:26.749 --> 00:19:29.419
Should I ask her to keep it a secret?

00:19:30.044 --> 00:19:32.046
What if she tells the whole school instead?

00:19:32.589 --> 00:19:33.965
No. What am I going to do?

00:19:36.634 --> 00:19:38.636
I asked if you've handed in your math assignment.

00:19:38.720 --> 00:19:41.222
If you don't do it today, you're bound to get more demerits.

00:19:41.306 --> 00:19:43.558
Right, I need to get on it.

00:19:43.641 --> 00:19:45.059
I'm going to do it later.

00:19:45.643 --> 00:19:46.477
Eui-ju.

00:19:46.561 --> 00:19:47.979
Don't forget, okay?

00:19:48.563 --> 00:19:49.397
Okay.

00:19:51.357 --> 00:19:52.734
What's wrong? Is everything okay?

00:19:53.693 --> 00:19:54.527
Yeah.

00:19:55.486 --> 00:19:57.238
The math thing is distracting her.

00:19:57.322 --> 00:19:59.157
The rolled omelet is amazing.

00:20:10.418 --> 00:20:12.837
One of the main characters is a math genius.

00:20:12.921 --> 00:20:15.214
Apparently, his personality is just like Mr. Ga's.

00:20:16.007 --> 00:20:17.008
Isn't that weird?

00:20:17.926 --> 00:20:19.218
Eui-ju, what do you think?

00:20:19.969 --> 00:20:22.263
If it were you, do you think you could hide it?

00:20:22.847 --> 00:20:25.642
What if the whole school knows by tomorrow?

00:20:41.658 --> 00:20:44.118
CHAPTER 41: NOTHING STAYS A SECRET FOREVER

00:20:44.202 --> 00:20:45.536
-Hey, come here! -She's sleeping again.

00:20:45.620 --> 00:20:47.330
Hey, where have you been?

00:20:47.413 --> 00:20:49.290
-Where did you go? -Did you hit the snack bar?

00:20:50.208 --> 00:20:52.085
-We won't take no for an answer. -Hand it over.

00:20:56.422 --> 00:20:58.132
-Hello. -Hello.

00:21:02.261 --> 00:21:04.806
All right. Today is our first lesson on "Gongmudohaga."

00:21:04.889 --> 00:21:06.432
Turn to page 168.

00:21:07.600 --> 00:21:08.893
Mr. Yoon.

00:21:09.560 --> 00:21:10.770
Yes?

00:21:10.853 --> 00:21:12.438
Is she going to expose me in class?

00:21:13.398 --> 00:21:14.816
She won't, right?

00:21:14.899 --> 00:21:16.943
Is this poem the last work covered on the exam?

00:21:17.026 --> 00:21:18.194
Yes, that's right.

00:21:23.825 --> 00:21:24.742
Are you okay?

00:21:25.493 --> 00:21:26.703
Something's up, isn't it?

00:21:27.453 --> 00:21:28.538
It's nothing.

00:21:29.831 --> 00:21:31.958
"My beloved, don't cross that river."

00:21:32.583 --> 00:21:35.086
"Alas, you crossed the river."

00:21:35.795 --> 00:21:36.754
Should I

00:21:37.714 --> 00:21:39.465
just confess everything?

00:21:40.049 --> 00:21:44.262
Isn't that better than waiting nervously for the other shoe to drop?

00:21:47.015 --> 00:21:48.266
Or should I just…

00:21:50.268 --> 00:21:53.896
DO YOU WANT TO DELETE THIS NOVEL?

00:22:36.105 --> 00:22:37.273
No way.

00:22:55.124 --> 00:22:56.125
Hey, Eui-ju.

00:22:56.209 --> 00:22:59.670
On my way to the art academy yesterday, I snapped this photo of a cat.

00:22:59.754 --> 00:23:00.963
Isn't it cute?

00:23:04.383 --> 00:23:05.885
Is something wrong?

00:23:06.594 --> 00:23:07.929
Not at all.

00:23:15.436 --> 00:23:16.604
SPECIAL OFFER FOR THE INTERNET

00:23:21.109 --> 00:23:22.276
-Hey. -Gosh.

00:23:23.069 --> 00:23:24.612
You're acting really weird.

00:23:24.695 --> 00:23:25.696
What's going on?

00:23:26.322 --> 00:23:27.990
I said it's nothing, didn't I?

00:23:33.496 --> 00:23:35.373
Sorry, I was just surprised.

00:23:37.834 --> 00:23:39.669
Oh, okay.

00:23:44.590 --> 00:23:47.135
So, f(x) equals the integral of…

00:23:48.344 --> 00:23:51.013
X plus three x squared.

00:23:51.722 --> 00:23:52.849
Then, the x cubed.

00:23:54.433 --> 00:23:55.726
This equals negative ten.

00:23:56.727 --> 00:23:58.646
So, put negative one into the formula,

00:23:58.729 --> 00:24:00.940
and you get negative ten. Not too difficult, right?

00:24:01.023 --> 00:24:02.275
-No, sir. -No, sir.

00:24:02.358 --> 00:24:03.442
Let's stop here for today.

00:24:03.526 --> 00:24:04.569
Great job.

00:24:04.652 --> 00:24:06.404
-Thank you. -Thank you.

00:24:08.698 --> 00:24:10.825
-Goodbye. -Goodbye.

00:24:19.458 --> 00:24:21.294
Mr. Ga, can I ask you a question?

00:24:23.045 --> 00:24:27.383
For number 356, I get that C is six, but I'm not sure where to go from there.

00:24:28.134 --> 00:24:29.427
I'm sure you've got this.

00:24:29.510 --> 00:24:30.720
It's just a bit confusing.

00:24:32.054 --> 00:24:35.224
If you integrate here, g(x) equals x cubed plus four, right?

00:24:36.017 --> 00:24:38.644
So you just need to find the value when g is negative two.

00:24:39.562 --> 00:24:43.107
Always remember that we can use the Product Rule this way.

00:24:43.191 --> 00:24:44.525
-Okay. -Good job today.

00:24:45.026 --> 00:24:45.860
Mr. Ga.

00:24:49.071 --> 00:24:50.990
I brought this for you.

00:24:53.826 --> 00:24:55.203
You really didn't have to.

00:24:58.539 --> 00:24:59.665
Please don't do so again.

00:25:00.291 --> 00:25:01.542
Okay.

00:25:06.088 --> 00:25:08.132
-No difficulties following the class? -Not yet.

00:25:08.841 --> 00:25:09.884
All right, then.

00:25:14.055 --> 00:25:15.139
Why are you still here?

00:25:16.599 --> 00:25:19.143
-Well… -I guess you need to talk to Mr. Ga.

00:25:19.227 --> 00:25:21.270
If it's a question, you could've asked in class.

00:25:26.901 --> 00:25:29.028
-I'll leave you to it. -Okay.

00:25:38.246 --> 00:25:39.330
What is it?

00:25:42.959 --> 00:25:44.543
Mr. Ga, I really think

00:25:45.753 --> 00:25:48.756
I should take a break from writing my web novel.

00:25:50.675 --> 00:25:51.509
Why?

00:25:52.802 --> 00:25:53.636
Well,

00:25:54.262 --> 00:25:56.138
I should focus on studying.

00:25:56.806 --> 00:25:59.684
Also, I keep forgetting to do my homework.

00:26:23.791 --> 00:26:25.876
Why have you lost confidence? That's not like you.

00:26:26.711 --> 00:26:27.962
It's not like that.

00:26:28.587 --> 00:26:29.505
It's just…

00:26:30.047 --> 00:26:32.258
I thought a short break would do me good.

00:26:34.093 --> 00:26:36.429
I don't know what gave you that idea,

00:26:37.096 --> 00:26:39.056
but think back on when you first started writing.

00:26:40.182 --> 00:26:42.893
Look back on why you started writing this novel in the first place

00:26:42.977 --> 00:26:44.562
and how you felt then.

00:26:46.814 --> 00:26:48.232
That's where you'll find the answer

00:26:49.025 --> 00:26:52.111
on whether you really need a break, or if that's just an excuse.

00:26:56.449 --> 00:26:57.908
You said you would keep at it

00:26:58.701 --> 00:26:59.869
and get better.

00:27:00.995 --> 00:27:02.330
Isn't that why you started?

00:27:04.915 --> 00:27:07.335
I'm not sure if I'm doing the right thing.

00:27:08.753 --> 00:27:12.131
Still, you've put my mind at ease, sir.

00:27:17.136 --> 00:27:18.220
Drink this and cheer up.

00:28:48.727 --> 00:28:50.729
Subtitle: Paul Carver

